reviewText: Outstanding history of King's College Choir

Very well-done hour-long documentary on King's College Choir (and the chapel itself).  This ran on American television back in the 1980's.  The sound is satisfactory, but the picture is not the clearest.  But the content makes up for that.
Rather poor image quality. Sound is fine though. DVDs by King's College are always worth purchasing. I am glad I did.
